<subSubSection id="B6DC9EABFFF1FFABFF3677AED919FBC2" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFF1FFABFF3677AED919FBC2" blockId="64.[188,794,649,1089]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF1FFABFF3677AED954FD22" bold="true" box="[189,300,649,673]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Comment</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FFF1FFABFECA77ADDA54FD22" author="HLAVAC, P. &amp; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M." box="[321,556,649,677]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref77416" refString="HLAVAC, P.; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M. 2011: World catalogue of the species of the tribe Lomechusini (Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Zootaxa 3075: 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="2011">HLAVÁČ et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
list 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF1FFABFDE377AED9EEFD42" authority="(GISTEL, 1857)" baseAuthorityName="GISTEL" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polyporina">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF1FFABFDE377AED891FD42" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Drusilla polyporina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FFF1FFABFF76778ED9F7FD42" author="GISTEL, J. N. F. X." box="[253,399,681,705]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" refId="ref77353" refString="GISTEL, J. N. F. X. 1857: Achthundert und zwanzig neue oder unbeschriebene wirbellose Thiere. - Straubing: Verlag der Schorner'schen Buchandlung: 94 pp." type="book" year="1857">GISTEL, 1857</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
as a nomen dubium. The original description, which is based on an unspecified number of 
<typeStatus id="217D7382FFF1FFABFF3677CDD961FC81" box="[189,281,746,770]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">syntypes</typeStatus>
from “Styriae”, is practically devoid of relevant information. All that is specified is the coloration (“nigerrima; antennis thorace elytris et pedibus fuscis”), the size, and that it is close to 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF1FFABFE27766DDA32FCE2" baseAuthorityName="FABRICIUS" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[428,586,841,865]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canaliculata">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF1FFABFE27766DDA32FCE2" box="[428,586,841,865]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. canaliculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The type material is presumably lost (ASSING 2008). However, it can be inferred that the type material of 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF1FFABFD9076ADDAD3FC22" baseAuthorityName="GISTEL" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[539,683,905,929]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polyporina">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF1FFABFD9076ADDAD3FC22" box="[539,683,905,929]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. polyporina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF1FFABFEA7768DD9B1FC42" baseAuthorityName="FABRICIUS" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[300,457,937,961]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canaliculata">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF1FFABFEA7768DD9B1FC42" box="[300,457,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. canaliculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only representative of the genus distributed in what used to be “Styria” (
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FFF1FFABFD4076EED97BFB82" author="ASSING, V." pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="111 - 149" refId="ref76224" refString="ASSING, V. 2005 b: On the western Palaearctic species of Drusilla LEACH, with special reference to the species of the eastern Mediterranean (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 75: 111 - 149." type="journal article" year="2005">ASSING 2005b</bibRefCitation>
). In order to dispose of the doubtful 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF1FFABFD2676CDD891FBA2" baseAuthorityName="GISTEL" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polyporina">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF1FFABFD2676CDD891FBA2" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. polyporina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is placed in synonymy with the senior synonym 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF1FFABFF36710DD922FBC2" baseAuthorityName="FABRICIUS" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[189,346,1065,1089]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canaliculata">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF1FFABFF36710DD922FBC2" box="[189,346,1065,1089]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. canaliculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
